This is a timetable generator project for a college scheduling system.

Backend: Python, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Alembic, PostgreSQL, Celery, Redis
Frontend: React (Vite), Tailwind CSS
Solver: Google OR-Tools CP-SAT algorithm (Person 2 handles this)

Database entities (updated ER diagram with suggested additions):
- Class (class_id, class_name)
- Subject (subject_id, subject_name, periods_per_week, class_id, subject_type)
- Teacher (teacher_id, teacher_name, max_periods_per_day)
- Room (room_id, room_number, room_type)
- TimeSlot (slot_id, day, period_number)
- TeacherSubject (teacher_id, subject_id)  — many to many bridge
- TeacherAvailability (teacher_id, slot_id, is_available)
- Timetable (timetable_id, class_id, subject_id, teacher_id, slot_id, room_id)
- Constraint (constraint_id, constraint_name, constraint_type, parameters_json)

Coding conventions:
- Use snake_case for Python, camelCase for JavaScript
- All FastAPI routes return JSON
- Use async functions in FastAPI where possible
- Keep each file focused on one responsibility
- SQLAlchemy models go in app/models/
- Pydantic schemas go in app/schemas/
- Route handlers go in app/api/
